            <thetext>This is a follow-up from bug#7573. Currently, the AnimationHandle only allows 
you to stop and resume an animation, but not to reset it to the initial state. 
I.e. you can never reset an animation once it has started. But in some 
situations this might be exactly what you want to do, e.g. when you need to 
stop an animation but don&#39;t want to finish it. In such a case the animation 
would &quot;hang&quot; somewhere midways.</thetext>
